created.title: created
created.desc: Returns the `traits.createdAt` and falls back on `traits.created`, `properties.createdAt` and `properties.created`. Note that it will return a `Date` object.

email.title: email
email.desc: Tries to return the `traits.email` and if it is not defined, it will check the `groupId`  and return that if it is a valid email.

traits(aliases).title: traits(aliases)
traits(aliases).desc: Returns all the `traits`. You can also pass an optional object defining aliases. Note that the Facade will also add `traits.id` which is the same as `groupId`.

properties.title: properties
properties.desc: Returns the `traits` and fallsback on `properties` or `{}`.
